def count_hills_valleys(nums):
    count = 0
    for i in range(1, len(nums) - 1):
        if (nums[i] > nums[i - 1] and nums[i] > nums[i + 1]) or (nums[i] < nums[i - 1] and nums[i] < nums[i + 1]):
            count += 1
    return count
```


    The algorithm iterates through the array from the second element to the second-last element. For each element, it checks whether it is part of a hill or a valley. This is done by comparing the current element with its left and right neighbors. If the element is larger than both neighbors, it is part of a hill; if it is smaller than both neighbors, it is part of a valley. The count is incremented when the element is part of a hill or a valley. This process is repeated for all elements in the specified range. Finally, the count of hills and valleys is returned.

